// ğŸ“Œ What is Bubble Sort?
// Bubble Sort repeatedly steps through the array, compares adjacent elements, and swaps them if they are in the wrong order. This process continues until the array is fully sorted.

// ğŸ”¹ Example:
// Think of bubbles rising in water â€“ the larger bubbles (numbers) gradually move to the top (end of the array), just like in this sorting algorithm! ğŸŒŠ

// ğŸ› ï¸ Bubble Sort in JavaScript
