// ğŸ§ How Does This Work? (Step-by-Step Example)
// For array = [4, 2, 7, 1]

// 1ï¸âƒ£ Compare 4 & 2 â†’ Swap â†’ [2, 4, 7, 1]
// 2ï¸âƒ£ Compare 4 & 7 â†’ No swap
// 3ï¸âƒ£ Compare 7 & 1 â†’ Swap â†’ [2, 4, 1, 7]
// 4ï¸âƒ£ Repeat until fully sorted! âœ…

// â³ Understanding Time Complexity
// ğŸ”¹ Worst Case: O(nÂ²) â€“ When the array is reversed.
// ğŸ”¹ Best Case: O(n) â€“ When the array is already sorted.

// ğŸ’¡ Bubble Sort is easy to understand but not the most efficient sorting algorithm.

// ğŸ’¡ Key Takeaways
// âœ” Simple sorting algorithm but inefficient for large datasets.
// âœ” Best for learning sorting logic & understanding swaps.
// âœ” Time Complexity: O(nÂ²), Space Complexity: O(1) (in-place sorting).

